# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# Every variable is optional — the site builds and runs fine without any
# of them, and each feature degrades gracefully when its variable is unset:
#   • No GA4 ID          → analytics events simply aren't sent (site still works)
#   • No EmailJS keys    → the contact form falls back to opening the visitor's
#                          own email client instead of sending silently
#   • No GitHub username → defaults to "Rohitdixitcs"
#
# All Vite env vars MUST be prefixed with VITE_ to be exposed to the browser.
# Never put secret/private keys here — anything in this file ships to the
# client bundle. EmailJS's "public key" and a GA4 Measurement ID are
# designed to be public, so this is safe.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Analytics 4 — from GA4 Admin → Data Streams → your stream → Measurement ID
VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# EmailJS — from https://dashboard.emailjs.com (Email Services / Email Templates / Account → API Keys)
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# GitHub username used by the live GitHub stats section
VITE_GITHUB_USERNAME=Rohitdixitcs
